Three years in October, where has the time gone 😭🫶 We’ve spent nearly seven years together and the one thing I can truly say that makes a difference is embracing each and every stage. 

Time goes quicker and quicker the older you get. With each new change and decision you make - things feel like gradual changes until you look back three years later and realize just how MUCH things have changed. I’ve always been a huge proponent of appreciating the then & now. It’s so easy to get caught up on the next stage and forget about what’s right in front of you. Here’s to this stage 🥂 

#marriagetips #marriedlife #happymarriage #happycouple #marriedcouple #relationshiptips

We have been on this journey the last few years but it feels like time is speeding up and it’s time to really get the most out of the now 🤍 I’ll be this documenting our dates, trips, and daily lives as well as our financial, personal, and physical goals for the future. If you’re in a similar period of life, lets connect and make the most out of this time 🥂 

#dinkfam #dinklifestyle #dinkvlog #dinkdiaries #marriedwithoutchildren #marriedwithoutkids #happymarriage #preparingforkids #dateideas #coupletips #coupleideas #relationshiptips

How do you know when you’ve found ‘the one’. My husband is truly my life partner and simply being next to him feels ‘right’. Your partner should always push you to be the best version of yourself and you should feel truly equipped to take on anything with them by your side. In my vows to Max I wrote “I would forever choose the worst day in the world with you by my side over the best day without you in my life” and I mean that. Life is a wild ride and you never know what will come your way but marriage is all about finding that person who is going to be by your side through it all 🤍

#marriedcouple #theone #relationshiptips #engagedcouple #lovestory #coupleadvice #marriageadvice #relationshipadvice

Memories > Material but like we also budget and plan for these things ✨ As crazy as it is to say, over the seven years we’ve been together, we do not spend much on material. We have kept our cars for quite some time (mine is from college and paid off). Our rent has only marginally increased over the last five years and we have continued to increase our incomes. I rent any ‘trendy’ clothing I wear and only buy clothing ‘basics’ for me. And we don’t spend money on luxury or designer goods pretty much ever. So while it may seem like our budget for date nights and vacations is high, it’s because we don’t spend money on other things. We save a large chunk, pay for all of our regular expenses, and then we factor in date nights into our regular monthly budget! If you need some structure, check out my monthly budget template on my Stan store. 🤍 

#datenights #couplescomedy #husbandandwife #marriedlife #dinklife #dualincomenokids

Way cheaper than T-Swift tickets so we will count this as a win 😆🤍 On the real though, seeing Max happy truly makes me happy. Seeing Max light up when Darius came out on stage and then dancing with Max to every song was a core memory I’ll never forget. Being married to your best friend and experiencing new moments is truly the best. I hope you and your partner are doing something for the first time soon (if you know you know hehe)🫶

Tbt to the first 20 years of my life and swearing I would never get married 😅🤍 I never understood the value of marriage because I grew up surrounded by unhealthy ones. 

I saw one truly ‘successful’ love story with my grandparents and then I saw the biggest heartbreak a human can feel when they were separated by life/death. I saw most of the marriages around me either end up in divorce or hatred. And when looking at divorce statistics, I said - “yeah I’m good”. I didn’t think about the advantages or what I would be missing because I didn’t know what it felt like to find ‘your person.’ I know now, that I was wrong and almost missed out on the best thing I could possibly experience. I love the sh*t out of Max because he makes living easier. He pushes me to be better. And life is generally more fun with him in my life. I couldn’t imagine a day without him now and I genuinely hope we kick the bucket at the same time so I never have to (dark humor) 😆🤍 

#marriedlife #happymarriage #husbandandwife #relationshipgoals #happyrelationship #marriagetips

Truly unhinged and I am in no way shape or form a financial professional so don’t take this as financial advice 😆 BUT, I’ve also seen a lot of couples opt for “separate” finances just because one person in the relationship feels like they spend more and that would create tension if they had combined bank accounts. Personally, I am in favor of having combined finances because it helps you set holistic goals and keeps you on the same page. Of course - do you and what is best in your relationship. In our relationship - I do the finances for the both of us. I also spend more. Which means we are never fighting about “who spends more” because I am planning a budget for both of us to spend on things we want each month. It also allows me to see exactly where we spend and where I can cut back. Of course, whoever does your finances should have some financial literacy and financial goals should be set as a couple. But idk, what are your thoughts? Combined incomes? Separate incomes? One person budgets? I’m curious, so let me know! 

#finances #marriagetips #marriedlife #marriage #combinedincomes

Since I share a lot of the ‘fun’ things we do, I figured I would share some ‘not so fun’ things we do. The reality is that these things build the foundation for us and allow us to do things like date nights and travel. 

For the first one, I don’t share it much but Max and I have always been very into taking care of our physical fitness. I used to work in Nutrition and Max has a degree in Kinesiology & was a Personal Trainer.  But we do not invest this much time into it because “we want to look good.” We do it because it’s essential to our mental health and is time that we are spending daily investing in ourselves - which is the theme for all of these. 

Our lives are not super interesting behind the scenes. We both work. We have chores. We do all the regular “not so fun” things anyone else does daily. It’s easy to see all the fun things we post on social media and think we are different, but this is what is going on behind the scenes to help us achieve our goals.

This country is breathtaking, full of genuine and kind people, has some of the best food on the planet, and a culture that is one-of-a-kind. Spain, you were an absolute treat. Not Twenty-two but we are about to be in Paris, baby. Heading to Paris tomorrow with a very full heart (& stomach) after the last four days in Bordeaux and Epernay 🇫🇷🍾🧀 Some advice for those traveling to France for the first time: don’t be intimidated, people are quite friendly and a large portion of the population does speak decent English! However, do your research and learn some basic French. Max made a cheat sheet with need to know phrases, what they mean, and how to pronounce them - lmk if you want me to share it! au revoir🤍

Paris, I absolutely adored all 40,000 steps we took together in the last 36 hours. I’m going to miss you but off to the next city & our last country (technically?) of the trip 🥹🤍 

Now I’m going to be honest, before coming to France (and specifically Paris) I had some preconceived notions that really kept me from prioritizing France on my ‘must visit’ list. Those being all the same stereotypes I’m sure most Americans have heard (people are snobby, must speak French, Parisians dislike Americans, Paris is dirty/unsafe, etc.). After 6 days in 3 cities, I’m happy to report back that those stereotypes (at least from what we experienced) couldn’t be further from the truth. We had a GREAT time in France and it’s a country I am so grateful to have experienced. We met so many kind, genuine people. Had amazing food and wine. The public transportation in France is some of the BEST we’ve used. We never once felt unsafe. And the history is absolutely unparalleled. France is truly spectacular and I encourage anyone to visit if you have the chance 🇫🇷🥂 

Most importantly, I hope this serves as a reminder to experience everything for yourself and to form your own opinions! There’s so much beauty in the world if you choose to see it.

9 countries and countless cities together 🥹🤍 I will FOREVER say the number one thing every couple should do (if they can) before getting married is to travel together. Everytime we travel we experience SO much life in such a short time. The joy of experiencing new things together, the struggles of figuring new things out, and all the silly moments in between. There’s truly nothing like it and I’m beyond blessed to have the best partner through it all! As most of you know we don’t have kids yet, but when we do I will be so proud to show them the world and everywhere we’ve been. 🤍 

#dinklife #travelingtogether #coupleswhotravel #traveltips #husbandandwife #marriagetips #marriedlife

The list goes on 😩🤍 Looking back at this year there’s a few things I feel particularly grateful for: 1) That we expanded our ‘family’ and got a pet 2) That I married the best human ever. 🤍 

This year was a wild ride for me in a lot of ways, but where I was sometimes mentally or physically absent, Max really made it his mission to take care of us. I’ve shared a lot about marriage and what not these last few years but if you ever take anything away from me - it’s to marry a true PARTNER. It won’t always be 50/50, sometimes one person will have to carry the bulk of the mental and physical load in the relationship. In our 7+ years together, it has gone back and forth between the two of us - but we always make sure to support one another without asking or needing to be told. In my opinion, the relationship isn’t the ‘hard’ part of marriage. Life is. And marriage is just about finding the right person to manage life with. 

Sorry for the sappy-ness on your timeline today 😭 End of the year always has me in my feels. Feeling extra grateful for the most important things today 🤍 

#marriedlife #dinklife #husbandandwife #husbandgoals #marriagegoals #marriedwithoutkids #dinkwac

Highlight reel vs reality 🫶 Based on the content I post, I always forget how little people know about Max and I and what our daily lives ACTUALLY look like. Of course we love our date nights and trips but there is always so much more going on behind the scenes. 

One of the reasons we are able to afford the trips and date nights AND still save is because we’ve cut back on things we don’t care about as much. Is it crazy that I still drive the same car I’ve had since college when I could afford a new car? Depends on who you ask. For me, I don’t see the value. I’m a big believer in not inflating your lifestyle just because you make more money. 

It’s so easy to see things on social media and compare. Just remember it’s all just a highlight reel 🤍

In marriage, and in most things in life, what you put in is what you will get out 🤍 Weddings are not the end goal of a relationship, but the start of a new chapter. As exciting as they are, they only last a day. And after that day is over you may wonder “so what’s next?” My number one tip for any newly wed is to keep investing in your relationship with one another. Post wedding is not the time to stop dating each other, working on your communication, and setting goals as a couple. The wedding day is just the beginning ✨

Things we do to keep our sheeeeit together 🫶 It’s not always fun and games over here - a lot of ‘having a healthy relationship’ requires consistent energy and a dedication to growth. There is so much that goes on BEHIND the scenes (and behind the date nights and trips). 

We both are very invested in our health and make it a priority to stay active and to eat quality food (why? Because being fit helps our physical and mental health). We budget regularly, talk out our conflicts before they become a problem, plan and strategize for our future, and genuinely just try to be there for one another as best as we can. 🤍 

Marriage is not always ‘50/50’ but it does always require 100% of your commitment.
